import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    chart = sns.barplot(x='month', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count by month?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
